// Regression: libFuzzer, 2026-04-18. Input `/module}module{struct` caused a
// BUS error in Parser::ParseStruct — SymbolTable::AddModule returns
// INVALID_INDEX on duplicate module names, but ParseModule stored that
// sentinel into currentModuleIndex while setting inModuleScope=true. A
// subsequent struct parsed inside the failed module scope then OOB-read
// symbolTable.modules[INVALID_INDEX] at bwsl_parser_soa.cpp:5961.
// Fix: ParseModule only enters module scope when AddModule succeeded; and
// ParseStruct's inModuleScope branch bounds-checks currentModuleIndex.
// Expected: compiler exits cleanly with parse errors, not a crash.
/module}module{struct
